Here's a proven pattern for runtime theme switching in .NET MAUI:

## 1. Define each theme as a `ResourceDictionary`

```xml
<!-- Resources/Styles/LightTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackground">#FFFFFF</Color>
    <Color x:Key="PrimaryText">#1A1A1A</Color>
    <Color x:Key="Accent">#0078D4</Color>
</ResourceDictionary>
```

Create matching `DarkTheme.xaml` and `HighContrastTheme.xaml` with the same keys but different values.

## 2. Create a theme service

```csharp
public enum AppTheme { Light, Dark, HighContrast }

public static class ThemeService
{
    public static void ApplyTheme(AppTheme theme)
    {
        var mergedDicts = Application.Current!.Resources.MergedDictionaries;

        // Remove existing theme dictionary (keep base styles)
        var existing = mergedDicts.FirstOrDefault(d => d.ContainsKey("PageBackground"));
        if (existing != null)
            mergedDicts.Remove(existing);

        // Add the new one
        mergedDicts.Add(theme switch
        {
            AppTheme.Dark         => new DarkTheme(),
            AppTheme.HighContrast => new HighContrastTheme(),
            _                     => new LightTheme()
        });

        // Persist choice
        Preferences.Set("app_theme", theme.ToString());
    }

    public static void LoadSavedTheme()
    {
        var saved = Preferences.Get("app_theme", nameof(AppTheme.Light));
        if (Enum.TryParse<AppTheme>(saved, out var theme))
            ApplyTheme(theme);
    }
}
```

## 3. Reference theme keys with `DynamicResource`

```xml
<ContentPage BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource PageBackground}">
    <Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryText}" Text="Hello" />
</ContentPage>
```

`DynamicResource` (not `StaticResource`) is critical — it re-evaluates when the dictionary changes.

## 4. Wire up the settings page

```xml
<Picker x:Name="ThemePicker" Title="Theme"
        ItemsSource="{Binding Themes}"
        SelectedIndexChanged="OnThemeChanged" />
```

```csharp
void OnThemeChanged(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    var selected = (AppTheme)ThemePicker.SelectedIndex;
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme(selected);
}
```

## 5. Load the saved theme at startup

In `App.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    ThemeService.LoadSavedTheme();
}
```

**Key points:**
- Same keys across all three dictionaries ensures consistency.
- `DynamicResource` enables instant switching without page reloads.
- `Preferences` persists the user's choice across sessions.
